1
00:00:00,075 --> 00:00:00,988
In JavaScript

2
00:00:01,175 --> 00:00:03,800
classes act as templates for creating objects

3
00:00:04,188 --> 00:00:07,513
They encapsulate data with code to work on that data

4
00:00:07,912 --> 00:00:10,512
Although JavaScript is prototype-based

5
00:00:10,750 --> 00:00:12,500
classes give a more intuitive

6
00:00:12,775 --> 00:00:14,537
object-oriented syntax

7
00:00:14,775 --> 00:00:19,725
which resembles class-based code structures in other programming languages like Java or C#

8
00:00:20,125 --> 00:00:22,550
This makes code more readable and maintainable

9
00:00:22,975 --> 00:00:27,475
thus allowing developers to easily implement inheritance and encapsulation

10
00:00:27,775 --> 00:00:29,750
crucial for software design patterns

